  "school": "ICT",
  "definition": "A local price peak where a candle's high is greater than those of its immediate neighbors, marking buy-side liquidity (stop orders). It defines market structure, serves as an anchor for Fibonacci retracement ranges (premium/discount), and its sweep with aggressive displacement below signals a bearish market structure shift. Used for reversal and continuation setups across multiple timeframes.",
  "identification_rules": [
    "Locate a candle whose high is greater than the highs of the candles immediately to its left and right on the chosen time frame.",
    "For reversal/reference purposes, confirm the swing high is swept (price trades above it) and then validated by a close below the series of up-close candles that formed it (a change in state of delivery); if it does not close below, it is not considered a confirmed swing high.",
    "Classify swing highs by structural significance: short-term (simple peak), intermediate-term (short-term highs on either side), or long-term (formed off a higher time frame reaction).",
    "Distinguish relevant swing highs from failure swings: a high left untaken during a directional move is a failure swing and is treated as a liquidity target, not a reversal point.",
    "When two or more swing highs form at similar levels with little separation, treat them as a single equal highs liquidity cluster.",
    "For Fibonacci range analysis, identify the most prominent peak in the price section; pair it with a corresponding swing low; if a new higher swing high prints, update the range anchor.",
    "Validate significance by checking that the swing high lies within a higher time frame point of interest (e.g., fair value gap, previous day high, order block).",
    "In the context of liquidity sweeps, ensure the swing high has not yet been traded through; a sweep must involve a break above followed by displacement back inside the range; a consolidation that merely approaches but does not pierce the high is not a sweep.",
    "Identify a three-candle formation where the middle candle's high is higher than the highs of the immediate left and right candles.",
    "Verify that the left and right candles have lower lows than the middle candle's low.",
    "Wait for the third candle to close to confirm the pattern completion.",
    "For enhanced reliability, optionally use a five-candle extension with additional left and right candles confirming lower highs and lower lows.",
    "找到一个候选高点，确认其左侧相邻高点低于该点",
    "等待右侧相邻高点也低于该点（后续价格未能超越该高点并回落），两侧均满足才视为有效 Swing High；确认前不可提前标记",
    "该高点上方聚集止损单（Buy Side Liquidity），可作为价格的吸引目标（Draw On Liquidity）",
    "在上升趋势中，后续 Swing High 应高于前一个（Higher High）；在下降趋势中，后续 Swing High 应低于前一个（Lower High）",
    "在看跌场景中，将斐波那契回撤工具从该 Swing High（fib 1）向下拖至对应的 Swing Low（fib 0）以标注分析区间",
    "当价格持续创新高时，需随之上移 Swing High 标记位置以跟踪扩展中的范围",
    "价格触及或突破该高点后，观察收盘价是否能收于高点上方：若收盘回落至高点下方，则确认失败位移（Failure To Displace），该 Swing High 转变为看跌偏差触发点"
  ],
  "trading_implication": "Swing highs serve as buy-side liquidity pools, providing targets for upside sweeps before reversals or continuation moves. In a bearish context, a sweep and subsequent displacement below the swing high confirms a market structure shift, setting up short entries with stops above the high. For range analysis, swing highs anchor Fibonacci retracement to define premium zones for selling. Unswept swing highs act as upside draw on liquidity for bullish continuations. They also validate order block and fair value gap entries. In an uptrend, price may sweep this liquidity before reversing; in a downtrend, a swing high below a supply zone confirms bearish continuation. Smart money targets these pools, pushing price above to trigger stops and then reverse. Traders use swing highs to anticipate liquidity sweeps for short entries after reversal or avoid placing stops near obvious swing highs. Swing High 有三类用途：①作为范围上边界，与 Swing Low 划定区间，斐波那契 0.5 为 Equilibrium，高于 0.5 为 Premium（寻找空头 PD Array），低于 0.5 为 Discount（寻找多头 PD Array）；②作为趋势判断基础，连续 Higher High 确认上升趋势，突破前 Swing High 视为 Break of Structure；③作为反转参考点，价格扫过后出现 Failure To Displace，预期看跌走势，止损置于高点上方，目标指向下方 Sell Side Liquidity。",
  "common_mistakes": [
    "Entering a short after a swing high sweep without a confirmed close below the up-close candles (change in state of delivery).",
    "Trading a swing high reversal without higher time frame point of interest confluence.",
    "Treating any local peak as a significant swing high instead of focusing on prominent, structurally relevant highs.",
    "Not updating the swing high anchor when price prints a new higher high.",
    "Misidentifying internal range liquidity (fair value gaps) as external range liquidity (swing highs).",
    "Assuming a consolidation that merely approaches the swing high constitutes a sweep.",
    "Placing stops at the order block level rather than above the swing high.",
    "Attempting a reversal short without an inversion fair value gap or clear displacement.",
    "Believing every sweep of a swing high signals reversal, overlooking continuation scenarios.",
    "Ignoring multiple swing highs with significant separation, marking only one target.",
    "Identifying a swing high without verifying a lower high on both sides of the three-candle sequence.",
    "Confusing a single high with a swing high; requires adjacent lower highs.",
    "未等待右侧更低高点收盘形成即提前确认 Swing High，导致趋势误判或区间标注不准确",
    "价格触及 Swing High 即认为反转，未等待收盘确认是否能收于高点上方，导致误判方向",
    "将任意局部高点标注为 Swing High，未严格确认两侧均有更低高点的结构条件",
    "将价格在区间内扫过的局部高点误认为有效 Swing High，实际上只是流动性扫荡而非结构性高点",
    "忽视更高时间框架偏差（Bias），在上升趋势中将 Swing High 仅作为反转点而非 Draw On Liquidity 使用",
    "忽视更高时间框架趋势，在低时间框架 Swing High 处过早做空，被更高时间框架回调行情止损出局",
    "仅识别单一范围，忽略价格区间内存在多个嵌套范围（ranges within ranges）",
    "价格创新高后未及时上移 Swing High 标记，导致范围划定滞后失效"
  ],
